This paper deals with natural language processing and knowledge mining, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of pre-trained language models and the focus on unsupervised techniques suggest that this paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method proposed in the paper involves ranking the validity of relational triples, which is a task that can be framed as a prediction problem and may be relevant to the field of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval, as it aims to extract knowledge from text, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
